text: @PranavHegdeHere @instagram Yeah credit is secondary. Consent is first. The biggest brands that I work with send me a form to give written consent for usage of each batch of images for online use, complete with usage terms, but "admin" of big feature page doesn't have the time to even ask. Unfortunate.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: @PranavHegdeHere @instagram Apart from individuals, these feature pages and meme accounts just use anything they want without permission, and with a lot of them the onus is on you to "DM for credit". Ridiculous. I just filed a copyright report on the tweet, let's see how long twitter takes.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: @PranavHegdeHere @instagram Yeah! But thankfully Instagram has a very efficient system for copyright violation reporting, filling it takes a bit,  but they act on it immediately. Twitter on the other hand, oh boy. I have to go to a desktop browser, sign in from there and then fill the form.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: @Athulja It's noise. Haha. When you try to sharpen over black it brings in these artifacts, but they do look like stars, so I over sharpened the black, let more of these artifacts come in, and put a lens blur on to give it that effect.

text:

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: As Charles stood on the top step of the Podium at Monza with the Tifosi going crazy and the media documenting it all, Mattia Binotto, Ferrari's team principal was shooting on his phone! I guess you can get a million photos but the one you make for yourself has a special place :)

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: What a drive by Charles, on the absolute limit, and over it a few times! To hold off Lewis through an entire GP and come off on top, that's something. And Seb oh man, something is going on with the poor guy. #F1 #ItalianGP

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: @jayjives @StarSportsIndia Tell me about it! Give me an ad free option, I'll pay! It's not like this is cricket and you have a gap between overs.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: And again. Two ad breaks in a 4 minute window, first time Bottas was in DRS, came back to hear he made a mistake and was 2 seconds down. You guys have got to find a better way. I'm just going to follow tweets now.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text: And again! Just before the break Leclerc 1st, Hamilton +.8 in 2nd, and Bottas +1.5 in 3rd. After the break Leclerc 1st, Bottas +2.2 in second, and Hamilton +1.5 in 3rd. Do they want you to miss the crucial bits? I'm usually on hotstar but still no WiFi at home.

name: Auditya Venkatesh
text:
And again! Leclerc and Hamilton catching up Vettel here, what kind of games can Vettel play to help his team mate.
@StarSportsIndia here's a game we will play, watch this ad.
